caption: This is such a great, cozy spot either inside or outside to have lunch or now dinner. It's tucked away in the alley behind the Main Street address making it not easy to find if you are not a local. Any sandwich I have had here has been superb and there is a wide range of them. The BLT comes with spinach pesto. And while the Pork Bahn Mi really isn't quite really one, it is tasty as all get out. Wine by the glass was excellent value.

Good! I got the fig and goat cheese panini, and at 7 bucks, the sandwich is a great deal including the chips or coleslaw that come with it. My partner got the black bean filo special, and it was packed with flavor and a rainbow of beautiful natural colors. The cafè is tucked away in the arts alley, and very artsy itself with cute paintings and an eye towards beachy decor. Def will be returning!
Great food. Would recommend over and over again.
Everything on the menu is amazing! And the staff is great.  Everything is so fresh and nourishing! We love eating here for lunch!
My favorite place to eat for lunch. Extremely friendly staff and wonderful food. Highly recommend it

Homemade bread, baked goods, salads, soups, sandwiches & more! Creative combinations. Absolutely wonderful staff. And where else can you get a delicious sandwich on homemade bread? Great spot for lunch especially when it's nice out and you can sit in the marketplace walkway.
The food is so tasty 😋 I am a meat eater and still got full with their veggie sandwich. My fav is their rainbow 🌈 sandwich, just loaded up with tasty color.
First time here I had a great experience with a friendly bartender and great staff. Food was absolutely excellent. Second time here and the food was even better. I

Great artisan type sandwiches!  had a hard time deciding because there were so many cool looking sandwiches on the menu. I ended up getting the golden finger. My wife got the tuna melt. The kids got a simple grilled cheese at a reduced price. All three were great! And we got these really cool bar things for dessert. Peanut butter and jelly bar and the caramel bar. Both were awesome. The caramel bar is half the size of the other but for good reason, it is so rich that if you had a whole one I think you'd get sick. Super yummy! I was surprised to find this here to be honest. Something I would expect more in a hipster neighborhood in Brooklyn or Northampton. It was really good! I'll come next time I'm in Springfield
Another dimension of flavor

Absolutely wonderful staff. And where else can you get a delicious sandwich on homemade bread? Great spot for lunch especially when it's nice out and you can sit in the marketplace walkway. Also next to wonderful boutique & yoga studio. Not to be missed!! They are now open some nights for dinner and have a liquor license.
Went last night to hear live music. They were great, loved the ambiance too. My daughter had a sandwich made, it looked amazing and she raved about it. Will definitely recommend Nosh.

I have been to this place three times and look forward to going back this week for lunch. The menu is totally creative and I enjoy that they use locally grown food as much as is possible in this area in developing their menu. Each time that I have been there, the service has been spot on and the consistency of food quality is the same each time. Reasonable prices. You will not be disappointed!

Great meal this afternoon - I got a veggie sandwich and a fresh glass of kombucha which was on tap. The waitress was kind and patient and helped adjust the entree for our preferences. They even brought out a small snack for my dog!  Quiet patio off of the main drag yet close to 91. Highly recommend if you’re in Springfield!

Nosh has fresh, delicious options you can feel good  about. Their pricing is reasonable and the portions generous. Every bit of flavor profile in my sandwich from the bread to the ample contents was fantastic. I had the Colorado Cruiser this time and we will surely be back again soon!!! My only regret about Nosh is they don’t yet have a second location in the Boston Rd/Parker St area so we can visit more often (everyday lunch?!? SO MUCH YES)
Food was fresh and tasty
Yum !
Nice place a little small but good customer service.
Great food great value great people fun setting

Updating my review, but not my stars.  Nosh is awesome across the board!  I've had wonderful sandwiches (Pulled Pork) and soups (Chicken Rice [might be the best in the City] - perfect for a chilly New England day).
I was SO happy to find a place with healthy food!  I had the Hot Friggin Goat sandwich with their gluten free bread and I left fat and happy!  Very filling and tasty.
Excellent place. Everything tastes so fresh and different. The Thanksgiving sandwich is to die for.

For dinner two of us had the veal Parm on the bone which is a huge meal and very delicious. Also we had Italian trio which is excellent with a meatball a sausage and braciole,  sausage and broccoli rabe with pasta and the wild mushrooms app which is fantastic. Charlie is a very welcoming manager, and Eamen is an excellent bartender.
Fresh, tasty food and wonderful service!
Very good light food
A gem in Springfield, MA. A must go to for lunch.
Great food. Prompt and friendly service. Good amount of food options to choose from, and it's hard to pick! Can't wait to try more!
I knew this part of the center existed but had never visited.  The atmosphere gives the city a modern feel, the food was very good and the staff were knowledgeable and approachable! 5 stars happily!
They should have more open space but I love there food

Homemade bread, baked goods, salads, soups, sandwiches & more! Creative combinations. Absolutely wonderful staff. And where else can you get a delicious sandwich on homemade bread? Great spot for lunch especially when it's nice out and you can sit in the marketplace walkway.  Also next to wonderful boutique & yoga studio. Not to be missed!!  Please note: It is hidden in the brick walkway behind Main Street address! Look for the sandwich board.
As the city has limited selection for places to have lunch, this is a hidden jem.
Delicious! Fresh! So many options! Adding this to the list of rotating lunch places 😁

I was not ready for this!!!!  One of my clients referred me to Nosh Cafe. I'm so glad that I checked it out!  I had the pleasure of trying the Namaste Black Bean Burger. This is not just any black bean burger. It is THE black bean burger of all bean burgers. It comes with onions, cheddar, avocado, mango, spinach, chipotle, on a focaccia bread. All of which were fresh. The mango was a different touch but it works and the flavors married together well. It was served with a side of thinly sliced cucumbers that appear to be in some sort of brine.  There was a bit of a wait for my order because it was lunch time rush, but well worth the wait!  I will definitely be going back to get this and to try their other selections.  Unfortunately there is no photo to accompany this review. I was hungry and had to nurse my baby. Next time!
We need more places like this in the world. Great menu. Good quality food!
Lovely atmosphere, great, inventive food
I've been a long time Nosh customer ever since Teri was just selling bread in her food cart. Her business has flourished wonderfully and the quality of the food never fails to impress me.

Very nice staff and excellent food options. Everything is fresh and delicious. Everything is made on premises. They also have great Monsoon roastery coffee, as well as craft beers and wine. Highly recommend this place!

I made my way to the counter to begin the plunge in what I wanted to eat for lunch. They had a burger for one of the specials but I am all burgered out from the winter. This place was screaming to me "try something new" so after bouncing ideas back and forth with the staff my eyes were fixated on ordering the "Tango Mango."
Great food and nice services
Excellent, excellent, excellent.

While the food is delicious and the staff pleasant, the employee who made my sandwich while wearing gloves handled her phone to take a photo for social media (phones are known to be dirtier than toilet seats) and then went back to touching my food but did not change her gloves. I almost asked her to remake the sandwich due to my disgust.

Pulled pork sandwich is good. I like their soups on a cold day. Salads are good. They use high quality ingriedients. Try to get there before the lunch rush, everything is made to order so a bit of a wait is common.
Ingredients were fresh, everything was very tasty

I’ll give a five star review, but am just writing to report that I could not find the place. Walked back and forth for a while in front of 1341 Main, which is the address listed.  Then went to a nice looking Mediterranean place across the street. Confused!
Friendly atmosphere. Food was wonderful. Nice, healthy options.
I love this place!  Fresh and homemade, you will not be disappointed.
Very, nice, great food and prices
Great sandwiches!

They had a burger for one of the specials but I am all burgered out from the winter. This place was screaming to me "try something new" so after bouncing ideas back and forth with the staff my eyes were fixated on ordering the "Tango Mango." Maybe it was how it was drawn on the chalkboard but fresh mango, spinach, pesto, fig jam & mozzarella not only sounded healthy
They catered our wedding and the food, service and the people were amazing! I would highly recomend!!
Great service and delicious lunch food. I recommend their green monster sandwich.
Best turkey sandwich I've ever had
Amazing food, reasonable prices, and great service. I'm definitely going to be a regular here.
Grilled cheese is so worth indulging on. Even picked up a pepperoni bread for entertaining at home.

Nosh is a more then just a cafe! They offer an incredible selection of hot paninis, cold sandwiches and baked goodies! They have a large selection of both vegeterian and carnivore delights! The staff is super friendly and welcoming and are ready to answer any question you may have! My favorite panini is the Buffalo Chicken, the bread is crunchy on the outside but so soft on the inside and the chicken is tender and flavorful. Now for the dessert, you must try the chocolate babka, it so good you have to get there early because its a sure sellout after the lunch crowds! #enjoy
So yummy perfect during jury duty
Great little sandwich spot in Springfield. Very creative combos and delicious!
Loved it here! Excellent food, drinks and atmosphere.  Everyone is welcoming and hospitable.
Great sandwiches!!
Great food great place
Outstanding and interesting food. Can't wait to go back and try more items on the menu!

Do yourself a favor and look no further for a lunch spot!  Hands down the best soups, sandwiches, and bowls in the area, and probably even the state!  Lots of vegetarian friendly options, everything made from scratch, and amazing desserts.  Thank you, from Colorado!
It is a great place and I have seen expand over time. The owner puts time and amazing energy into the place making it truly genuine. It has delicious food.
The sandwiches are delicious. The Colorado Cruiser is my go to sandwich here.
Yum. Yum. Yum. Fresh and  delicous
I loved everything here, and even came back again the next day

I recently visited this place. They have been so this location for 2 years and I never knew. Can I say heaven on Earth. I had a vegan meatball salad typically I know this sounds strange but OMG it was delicious. My friend had the sweet potato bowl she absolutely loved it. The staff was very curteous and made sure we felt welcomed, small Cafe but cozy and clean. I highly recommend this place they are located in the center of downtown Springfield in the market place near Mass Mutual Center. They're hours are Tuesday thru Saturday from 11-3pm. You will not leave disappointed another thing to note is they have something for everybody vegan and non vegan.
So welcoming and amazing food!!!
Too expensive. Food is fresh and Good, though. $10 for a sandwich?  Pricey.
Hidden gem of Springfield's lunch scene, there is NOTHING as good to be found!
Creative, healthy lunch made with care and expertise. Check Facebook for hours and they do not serve alcohol.
Sandwiches were amazingly delicious and the service was above and beyond. Decor was also very nice. Happy we came upon this place, would recommend.
Great food and atmosphere
Excellent food and the new dining area is perfect. Would love to see some gluten free/celiac options so my husband could join me.
Great place for a quick and affordable lunch near the MassMutual Center. There’s also a cute outdoor area to sit and eat. Got the Hot Friggin’ Goat, which was a delicious choice! Try this place out!
Everything there is EXCELLENT!!!

Fresh, tasty, friendly, affordable. They accommodated my lo carb diet by letting me turn any sandwich into a comparable salad. I went with the pulled pork and it was delicious. The slaw was great.  I LOVED the coconut Masala veggie soup as well.  If they were open later I would have gone back end of day to bring home a quart of the soup for dinner tonight.  Will lunch there  again soon.
They need more cowbell and clam chowder
